WEBVTT

00:08.469 --> 00:09.766
[Screaming]

00:19.613 --> 00:22.343
[Panting, Whimpering]

00:23.651 --> 00:25.881
[Doorknob Rattling]

00:32.192 --> 00:35.185
Leo! Leo! Come on. Get up. Let's go.

00:39.167 --> 00:42.193
Come on.

00:44.472 --> 00:46.201
Come on.

00:47.609 --> 00:50.737
No! Baby, come on. No.

00:50.812 --> 00:52.837
[Gasps]

00:54.349 --> 00:55.839
[Screams]

01:03.958 --> 01:06.950
No.
[Whimpering]

01:07.028 --> 01:08.461
Help me.

01:08.530 --> 01:12.091
- No!
- [Flesh Ripping]

01:12.167 --> 01:14.761
[Leo Gasping]

01:18.473 --> 01:21.465
[Pounding]

01:21.543 --> 01:23.738
[Echoing]

01:23.811 --> 01:26.609
Don't answer it.
There's a killer of women on the loose.

01:26.681 --> 01:28.114
[Pounding Continues]

01:30.318 --> 01:32.479
They caught that guy.
Threw him in the nuthouse.

01:32.554 --> 01:36.615
At Briarcliff. He's in there with Lana.

01:36.691 --> 01:39.524
I have to recant.
I'm recanting tomorrow.

01:39.594 --> 01:41.755
That might be tough.
You signed a document.

01:41.829 --> 01:43.888
I mean, not that anyone would blame you.

01:43.965 --> 01:46.957
- I'm gonna be sick.
- [Pounding Continues]

01:50.738 --> 01:53.502
Lois, don't.
You don't know who's out there.

01:54.676 --> 01:56.166
[Door Opens]

01:56.244 --> 01:58.974
[All]
Trick or treat!

01:59.047 --> 02:02.141
- Check out the mass murderers, Barb.
- Is today Halloween?

02:02.217 --> 02:06.381
Tomorrow. These little monsters are just
getting a jump on the competition.

02:06.454 --> 02:08.649
[Crying]
I don't have any candy.

02:08.723 --> 02:10.987
That's okay, Miss Peyser.
We'll come back tomorrow.

02:12.894 --> 02:16.796
The job, the kids, Halloween...

02:16.864 --> 02:18.354
Nothing makes sense without her.

02:19.334 --> 02:21.165
I just hate myself.

02:21.236 --> 02:24.535
Hey. You want me to stay over tonight?

02:25.707 --> 02:27.641
No. I... I'll be okay.

02:27.709 --> 02:31.611
[Sniffles] I just need a hot shower
and a good night's sleep.

02:31.679 --> 02:34.443
And tomorrow, I'm gonna get her
out of that place.

02:34.515 --> 02:37.006
You can say that you made a mistake.

02:37.085 --> 02:39.645
You got scared
and you hit the panic button.

02:39.721 --> 02:41.211
I have to get her out.

02:41.289 --> 02:44.622
<i>##[Pop]</i>

02:50.398 --> 02:54.664
<i>[Woman]
# Wishin' and hopin' and thinkin' and prayin' #</i>

02:54.736 --> 03:00.003
- <i># Plannin' and dreamin' his kisses will start #</i>
- [Shower Running]

03:00.074 --> 03:04.477
- <i># That won't get you into his heart #</i>
- <i>[Wind Whistling]</i>

03:04.545 --> 03:08.174
<i># So if you're thinkin' of how great #</i>

03:08.249 --> 03:12.549
- <i># True love is #</i>
- [Shower Off]

03:12.620 --> 03:14.588
<i># All you got to do is #</i>

03:14.656 --> 03:18.456
<i># Hold him and kiss him
and squeeze him and love him #</i>

03:18.526 --> 03:22.053
<i># Yeah, just do it and after you do #</i>

03:22.130 --> 03:25.725
<i># You will be his #</i>

03:25.800 --> 03:30.794
- [Window Closes]
- <i># You will be his #</i>

03:30.872 --> 03:35.775
<i># You will be his ##</i>

03:35.843 --> 03:37.435
[Gasps]
No!

03:37.512 --> 03:39.070
I'm... I'm a schoolteacher.

03:39.147 --> 03:40.910
The children... they won't understand.

03:41.616 --> 03:43.846
<i>[Screams]</i>

03:53.027 --> 03:55.291
<i>[Thunderclap]</i>

04:49.450 --> 04:51.145
- [Buzzer Sounds]
- [Clanking]

04:51.218 --> 04:52.776
[Man]
Come on. Get up.

04:52.853 --> 04:54.844
- [Knocking]
- Let's go. Come on.

04:56.223 --> 04:58.817
[Man #2]
Everybody, up and out! Now!

05:00.227 --> 05:03.287
- Get out of the bed.
- Come on. Stand out in the hall.

05:03.363 --> 05:06.491
[Inmates Shrieking, Groaning]

05:06.567 --> 05:08.535
- [Man] Right there.
- [Knocking]

05:11.371 --> 05:15.535
Room search, Miss Winters.
We find it keeps our charges honest.

05:15.609 --> 05:17.236
Food violation.

05:17.311 --> 05:18.642
Oh, Pepper.

05:18.712 --> 05:22.478
Now tell me, why is it we don't
allow food in the rooms?

05:22.549 --> 05:24.141
- Rats!
- That's right, Pepper.

05:24.218 --> 05:26.550
Why can't you get that through
your pointy little head? Huh?

05:26.620 --> 05:28.611
Hey, Sister.

05:28.689 --> 05:30.520
I have a cucumber in my room.

05:30.591 --> 05:32.081
But not because I was hungry.

05:32.159 --> 05:34.389
Stifle yourself, Shelley.
I'll be with you in a minute.

05:34.461 --> 05:37.760
- Find anything, Frank?
- No. Looks clean to me.

05:37.831 --> 05:39.822
Check the pillowcase.

05:40.734 --> 05:43.032
- [Sighs]
- [Frank] Uh-huh.

05:43.103 --> 05:44.934
Here we are.
[Chuckles]

05:49.243 --> 05:51.211
What do we have here?

05:52.079 --> 05:54.513
"October 28.

05:54.581 --> 05:57.209
Strip-searched and deloused.
Denied phone call."

05:57.284 --> 06:00.117
Who would you like to call, Miss Winters?

06:00.187 --> 06:03.247
- The American Civil Lesbians Union?
- [Chuckles]

06:03.323 --> 06:06.520
My editor knows I came here
to write a story...

06:06.593 --> 06:09.391
and, boy, do I have
a great scoop for him now.

06:09.463 --> 06:12.626
Ah, yes. You know, I've read your columns
about baked beans...

06:12.699 --> 06:14.860
gallivanting geese
who lost their way home.

06:14.935 --> 06:16.960
Riveting.

06:17.037 --> 06:19.767
Too bad your ambition
outweighs your talent.

06:22.509 --> 06:25.376
I don't need those, Sister.
I have an excellent memory.

06:25.445 --> 06:26.935
Yeah?

06:27.014 --> 06:28.504
We'll see about that.

06:29.383 --> 06:31.647
- [Knocking]
- [Door Opens]

06:31.718 --> 06:34.881
Ah. Sister Jude.

06:34.955 --> 06:38.152
Always a pleasure to lay
one's eyes on your sunny visage.

06:38.225 --> 06:41.592
- We have a problem.
- The little sapphic reporter?

06:41.662 --> 06:45.120
Yes. I noticed she'd been giving you fits.

06:45.199 --> 06:49.260
I believe that her memories
are her worst enemy.

06:49.336 --> 06:53.500
They're terrorizing her,
impeding repentance.

06:53.574 --> 06:56.509
So you would like to help
erase some of them.

06:56.577 --> 06:59.569
Bring her a little peace of mind. Correct.

06:59.646 --> 07:03.946
Is electroshock therapy
something you would suggest?

07:05.319 --> 07:07.184
My.

07:07.254 --> 07:09.415
That is quite a turnaround, Sister.

07:09.489 --> 07:12.356
The last time I suggested
electroshock therapy...

07:12.426 --> 07:15.190
you accused me
of being a sadistic barbarian.

07:15.262 --> 07:17.594
- I've prayed about it.
- Mm-hmm.

07:17.664 --> 07:19.154
When I wasn't praying for you...

07:19.233 --> 07:20.860
to find a halfway decent haberdasher.

07:22.436 --> 07:25.371
And I came to the understanding
that this therapy...

07:25.439 --> 07:29.637
is just another tool
in his bountiful tool chest.

07:29.710 --> 07:32.543
- Hmm.
- <i>[Lana] Get them off. Help me.</i>

07:32.613 --> 07:35.514
Help me! Please let me go. Help!

07:35.582 --> 07:39.382
[Screams]
Get off! Get off of me!

07:39.453 --> 07:41.546
This woman is a kidnapper.
She's a kidnapper.

07:41.622 --> 07:44.489
She blackmailed my lover
into committing me.

07:44.558 --> 07:46.958
Please help me!
I don't belong here! Get me out of here!

07:47.027 --> 07:49.052
You're right. She is a noisy one.

07:49.129 --> 07:53.862
Help me!
[Muffled Whimpering]

07:54.968 --> 07:57.562
[Electricity Humming]

07:57.638 --> 08:00.664
Given your interest, Sister,
perhaps you'd like to assist.

08:00.741 --> 08:02.732
Just hold these by her temple.

08:02.809 --> 08:04.470
You're not squeamish, are you?

08:06.413 --> 08:08.973
[Whimpering Continues]

08:12.286 --> 08:15.312
- [Powering Up]
- Sister.

08:19.559 --> 08:22.653
- [Electricity Crackling]
- [Moaning]

08:28.568 --> 08:33.335
- [Crackling Stops]
- [Moaning Continues]

08:34.607 --> 08:37.509
[Man]
Shh. Shh.

08:37.577 --> 08:39.408
[Moaning Quiets]

08:39.546 --> 08:43.038
<i>##[Woman Singing "Dominique"In French]</i>

08:51.158 --> 08:54.218
- [Man] Whoa. Whoa. Where you going?
- <i>##[Continues]</i>

08:55.595 --> 08:57.722
Gentlemen.

08:57.798 --> 08:59.857
I can handle it from here. Thank you.

09:02.369 --> 09:04.200
Mr. Walker, Dr. Oliver Thredson.

09:09.876 --> 09:11.605
<i>[Thredson]
Patient is 24 years old.</i>

09:11.678 --> 09:14.306
- All right if I call you Kit?
- Sure.

09:14.381 --> 09:16.212
- [Exhales]
- <i>Completed grades "K"through 12.</i>

09:16.283 --> 09:17.773
<i>No higher education.</i>

09:17.851 --> 09:20.251
<i>Patient is believed responsible
for the murders of multiple women...</i>

09:20.320 --> 09:21.810
<i>including his wife.</i>

09:21.888 --> 09:23.480
Seems unreasonable to me...

09:23.557 --> 09:26.185
that a man should be denied
the right to smoke.

09:26.259 --> 09:30.389
<i>Victim's bodies were discovered
in a remote field... drained of blood, decapitated.</i>

09:30.464 --> 09:33.262
<i>The murders may have started
as a purging of racial guilt...</i>

09:33.333 --> 09:35.961
<i>at what his conditioning
would have viewed as an illicit coupling.</i>

09:36.036 --> 09:37.799
Do you know why I'm here, Kit?

09:37.871 --> 09:39.839
You're the headshrinker
the courts sent to see if I'm crazy.

09:39.906 --> 09:41.806
If you say I am,
they leave me here to rot...

09:41.875 --> 09:44.605
and if you say I'm not,
they put me on trial and then fry me.

09:44.678 --> 09:46.373
- <i>Patient is manipulative.</i>
- <i>[Typing]</i>

09:46.446 --> 09:48.437
Trouble is...

09:48.515 --> 09:50.449
I'm not crazy.

09:50.517 --> 09:53.145
- And I didn't kill those ladies.
- What about your wife?

09:53.220 --> 09:55.017
Alma's not dead.
That body didn't have a head.

09:55.088 --> 09:57.818
None of the bodies had heads, Kit.

09:57.891 --> 09:59.854
Initially, you told
police that you were...

09:59.954 --> 10:01.019
I know what I said!

10:02.863 --> 10:05.423
But it wasn't Alma.

10:05.499 --> 10:08.093
See, I know that now,
'cause I'm starting to remember.

10:08.168 --> 10:09.692
And I saw her.

10:11.304 --> 10:13.431
After they took her, she was alive.

10:13.507 --> 10:15.304
- "They"?
- [Door Closes]

10:16.309 --> 10:17.970
The men from outer space?

10:19.713 --> 10:21.476
They have her.

10:21.548 --> 10:22.879
<i>[Typing]</i>

10:22.949 --> 10:27.784
<i>Diagnosis. Acute clinical insanity.</i>

10:28.688 --> 10:30.349
<i>[Typewriter Carriage Resets]</i>

10:33.794 --> 10:36.695
- [Rustling]
- [Gasps]

10:36.763 --> 10:38.697
Dr. Arden, you're like a shadow.

10:38.765 --> 10:40.596
How is my favorite little helper today?

10:40.667 --> 10:43.192
They had quite the ferocious
appetite last night.

10:43.270 --> 10:44.897
- Do you hear them?
- No.

10:44.971 --> 10:47.064
Expected to find the basket
torn to pieces.

10:47.140 --> 10:49.404
Please, Doctor. You must tell me...

10:49.476 --> 10:51.341
What are these creatures?

10:51.411 --> 10:53.003
All in good time.

10:53.079 --> 10:56.480
You haven't said anything
to Sister Jude, now have you?

10:56.550 --> 10:58.074
No, of course not. It's our secret.

10:58.151 --> 10:59.709
Good.

10:59.786 --> 11:02.619
A small token of my gratitude.

11:05.992 --> 11:07.323
Oh.

11:07.394 --> 11:08.884
Candy apple.

11:09.596 --> 11:11.086
Looks delicious, but...

11:11.164 --> 11:12.756
- Mmm. I can't.
- [Replaces Lid]

11:12.833 --> 11:14.926
Go ahead. Have a bite.

11:16.736 --> 11:19.204
Oh, Sister. Life is too short for regrets.

11:21.141 --> 11:22.699
Take a taste.

11:24.878 --> 11:27.438
No. I really shouldn't.
Sister Jude says sweets lead to sin.

11:27.514 --> 11:30.881
I said... take a taste.

11:40.927 --> 11:41.951
[Chuckles]

12:02.782 --> 12:04.977
<i>##[Woman Singing "Dominique"In French]</i>

12:05.719 --> 12:08.711
<i>[Electricity Crackling]</i>

12:08.788 --> 12:11.086
- [Whimpering]
- <i>[Crackling Continues]</i>

12:11.157 --> 12:13.591
- <i>##[Continues]</i>
- [Door Opens]

12:16.997 --> 12:18.624
<i>[Crackling Continues]</i>

12:21.468 --> 12:25.131
[Grace] Did you do what I said?
Did you toss your shit at him?

12:25.205 --> 12:27.230
- Did you at least spit at him?
- I can't do it.

12:27.307 --> 12:29.207
I can't fake crazy.

12:29.276 --> 12:31.642
What I need to do
is escape this place <i>now...</i>

12:31.711 --> 12:33.679
before he files that report
and I'm screwed.

12:33.747 --> 12:36.875
There is no escape.
I gave you your way out.

12:36.950 --> 12:39.851
Think. Think hard.

12:39.920 --> 12:43.879
There's got to be a way out of this place.
I need to find Alma.

12:43.957 --> 12:46.084
What about the bakery?
Aren't there delivery vans?

12:46.159 --> 12:50.789
[Grace] How does that work? You disguise
yourself as a giant loaf of pumpernickel?

12:54.334 --> 12:55.961
Sister Jude.

12:56.036 --> 12:57.560
I'm Dr. Oliver Thredson.

12:57.637 --> 12:59.832
Ah, the court-appointed psychiatrist.

12:59.906 --> 13:02.875
You've seen our killer of women,
I trust.

13:02.943 --> 13:04.501
So what's it gonna be?

13:04.578 --> 13:07.172
We gonna spare the taxpayers
the expense of a trial...

13:07.247 --> 13:10.080
or will I have a bed opening up?

13:10.150 --> 13:12.550
I haven't made a determination yet.

13:12.619 --> 13:15.611
Might we speak privately
about the conditions here?

13:15.689 --> 13:19.489
Conditions?
What conditions might those be?

13:19.559 --> 13:22.687
In just the short time that I've been here,
I have witnessed appalling things:

13:22.762 --> 13:24.161
- [Blows Landing]
- <i>abuse-</i>

13:24.230 --> 13:25.720
- [Electricity Crackling]
- [Muffled] Help me!

13:25.799 --> 13:26.857
<i>Malpractice.</i>

13:26.933 --> 13:29.299
- Candidly, I'm shocked.
- It's a madhouse, Doctor.

13:29.369 --> 13:30.583
What did you expect?

13:30.683 --> 13:33.635
I expected some form
of treatment, therapy.

13:33.707 --> 13:38.007
Sister, your hospital still administers
electroshock therapy to treat homosexuality.

13:38.078 --> 13:41.377
It's barbaric. Behavior modification
is the current standard.

13:41.448 --> 13:43.382
Tomato, "tomahto."

13:43.450 --> 13:46.419
You know, Dr. Thredson,
let me remind you.

13:46.486 --> 13:49.922
Your job here is
to write a recommendation to the court...

13:49.990 --> 13:53.323
regarding the sanity of one patient.

13:53.393 --> 13:57.056
So I suggest you do your job
and let me do mine.

13:57.130 --> 13:59.826
[Door Opens, Closes]

13:59.899 --> 14:01.730
Now if you'll excuse me...

14:01.801 --> 14:06.170
there's another unfortunate family
who requires our care.

14:12.312 --> 14:15.213
Jed's been a good boy.
He's always listened.

14:15.281 --> 14:16.873
He's never talked back.

14:16.950 --> 14:19.612
Our problem started a month ago...

14:19.686 --> 14:21.745
Mrs. Potter, you needn't worry.

14:21.821 --> 14:24.221
Good boys gone bad
is my area of expertise.

14:24.290 --> 14:26.724
I've had great success in curbing
the chronic masturbator.

14:26.793 --> 14:28.351
[Door Opens]

14:29.629 --> 14:32.063
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to interrupt.

14:32.132 --> 14:34.396
We haven't finished
our conversation, Sister Jude.

14:34.467 --> 14:36.298
I didn't realize you had company.

14:36.369 --> 14:39.361
I'm Dr. Thredson, psychiatrist here.
I'm at your service.

14:39.439 --> 14:41.430
You need to leave, Doctor.

14:41.508 --> 14:43.908
Sister Jude, please.
Our boy is troubled.

14:43.977 --> 14:46.775
- We could use a doctor's opinion.
- [Sighs]

14:51.785 --> 14:53.844
- [Thredson] How can I help?
- [Sighs]

14:55.422 --> 14:57.049
Jed just turned 17.

14:57.123 --> 14:59.956
Over the last month,
he's grown listless and moody.

15:00.026 --> 15:02.051
Sometimes he doesn't
get up from bed for days.

15:02.128 --> 15:04.961
And then, the next moment,
it's like someone tied a live wire to his body.

15:05.031 --> 15:08.296
Adolescence can be a time
of conflict and rebellion.

15:08.368 --> 15:12.737
No, Doctor. Jed... sees things.

15:12.806 --> 15:15.639
He hears voices that aren't there.

15:15.709 --> 15:18.837
I'm afraid he'll bring us harm.

15:18.912 --> 15:21.608
Yesterday, we heard terrible cries
coming from the barn.

15:21.681 --> 15:23.342
[Screeching]

15:23.416 --> 15:25.611
<i>When I got there,
I found Jed covered in blood...</i>

15:25.685 --> 15:28.176
<i>Speaking a language
no one could understand.</i>

15:28.254 --> 15:30.779
[Shouting]

15:30.857 --> 15:32.449
<i>Then I saw what he had done.</i>

15:32.525 --> 15:36.359
He had ripped open the belly
of our best Guernsey.

15:36.429 --> 15:38.590
- Jed?
- [Roars]

15:39.666 --> 15:41.293
Ate her heart.

15:46.072 --> 15:48.131
It was unholy. It was...

15:48.208 --> 15:51.041
It was like some <i>thing...</i>

15:51.111 --> 15:55.275
had stepped inside my boy's body
and taken over his soul.

15:56.950 --> 15:58.383
Nothing?

15:59.719 --> 16:04.122
For a man whose profession
relies on talk, talk, talk...

16:04.190 --> 16:06.454
you appear to be at a loss
for words, Doctor.

16:06.526 --> 16:10.656
I... I would need to see him
in order to provide an accurate diagnosis.

16:10.730 --> 16:12.823
- We brought him here.
- Let's go see the boy now.

16:17.303 --> 16:18.964
Dr. Thredson.

16:19.038 --> 16:21.598
You are but a guest in our institution.

16:21.674 --> 16:25.974
<i>Don't</i> wear out your welcome the first day.

16:29.249 --> 16:32.082
[Growling]

16:33.486 --> 16:37.320
[Whimpering]
Mother, where am I? I'm scared.

16:39.559 --> 16:42.153
This is a hospital.
Doctors are here to help you.

16:42.228 --> 16:44.355
- [Croaking]
- Jed?

16:44.430 --> 16:46.091
[Switch Clicks]

16:47.167 --> 16:48.225
- [Roars]
- [Gasps]

16:49.836 --> 16:51.599
[Whimpers]

16:51.671 --> 16:55.505
[Speaking Unknown Language]

16:55.575 --> 16:57.372
Jed needs to be immediately medicated.

16:57.443 --> 17:01.573
[Continues In Unknown Language]

17:02.549 --> 17:04.107
No, Doctor.

17:04.184 --> 17:06.778
That's not what this boy needs.

17:13.459 --> 17:17.656
[Lana Breathing Heavily]
This hurts my burns.

17:17.730 --> 17:19.925
[Grace]
The harder you fight, the hotter it feels.

17:22.901 --> 17:25.425
[Lana]
What are you doing under there?

17:25.503 --> 17:28.268
Colonel Mustard
in the library with the wrench.

17:47.459 --> 17:49.427
I like the view from this window.

17:50.696 --> 17:54.427
All the bare trees, bleak and beautiful.

17:54.500 --> 17:56.593
Do you ever dream of escaping?

17:56.669 --> 17:59.365
[Scoffs]
All you new people.

17:59.438 --> 18:00.928
There is no way out.

18:01.006 --> 18:03.941
- What if I said I know a way?
- You'd be full of shit.

18:07.312 --> 18:10.770
There's a tunnel. It's real.

18:12.284 --> 18:13.774
I came in through it.

18:13.852 --> 18:16.753
Wow. They really messed with your mind.
What meds are you on?

18:16.822 --> 18:20.053
I need someone to help me
pull off an escape.

